  "prompt": "Money laundering has to be illegal, right?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries. It is a financial crime that involves disguising the origins of money obtained through illegal activities (such as drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear as if it comes from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and prison sentences. Most countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to prevent and prosecute such activities.",
